accountOverdraftLimit.description: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

accountablePerson.label: accountablePerson
accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

acquireLicensePage.label: acquireLicensePage
acquireLicensePage.description: Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

acquiredFrom.label: acquiredFrom
acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

acrissCode.label: acrissCode
acrissCode.description: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

actionAccessibilityRequirement.label: actionAccessibilityRequirement
actionAccessibilityRequirement.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

actionApplication.label: actionApplication
actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

actionOption.label: actionOption
actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

actionPlatform.label: actionPlatform
actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

actionStatus.label: actionStatus
actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

actionableFeedbackPolicy.label: actionableFeedbackPolicy
actionableFeedbackPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsrooms), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

activeIngredient.label: activeIngredient
activeIngredient.description: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

activityDuration.label: activityDuration
activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

activityFrequency.label: activityFrequency
activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

actor.label: actor
actor.description: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

actors.label: actors
actors.description: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

addOn.label: addOn
addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

additionalName.label: additionalName
additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

additionalNumberOfGuests.label: additionalNumberOfGuests
additionalNumberOfGuests.description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

additionalProperty.label: additionalProperty
additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

additionalType.label: additionalType
additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label should follow the schema.org style guide

additionalVariable.label: additionalVariable
additionalVariable.description: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

addressCountry.label: addressCountry
addressCountry.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

addressLocality.label: addressLocality
addressLocality.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

addressRegion.label: addressRegion
addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

administrationRoute.label: administrationRoute
administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

advanceBookingRequirement.label: advanceBookingRequirement
advanceBookingRequirement.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

adverseOutcome.label: adverseOutcome
adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or otherwise life-threatening or requiring immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriousAdverseOutcome instead.

affectedBy.label: affectedBy
affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

affiliation.label: affiliation
affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

afterMedia.label: afterMedia
afterMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

agent.label: agent
agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

aggregateRating.label: aggregateRating
aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

albumProductionType.label: albumProductionType
albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

albumReleaseType.label: albumReleaseType
albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

alcoholWarning.label: alcoholWarning
alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

algorithm.label: algorithm
algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

alignmentType.label: alignmentType
alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

alternativeHeadline.label: alternativeHeadline
alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

alternativeOf.label: alternativeOf
alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

alumniOf.label: alumniOf
alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

amenityFeature.label: amenityFeature
amenityFeature.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

amountOfThisGood.label: amountOfThisGood
amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

announcementLocation.label: announcementLocation
announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

annualPercentageRate.label: annualPercentageRate
annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

answerCount.label: answerCount
answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

answerExplanation.label: answerExplanation
answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

antagonist.label: antagonist
antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

appearance.label: appearance
appearance.description: Indicates an occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

applicableCountry.label: applicableCountry
applicableCountry.description: A country where a particular merchant return policy applies to, for example the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

applicableLocation.label: applicableLocation
applicableLocation.description: The location in which the status applies.

applicantLocationRequirements.label: applicantLocationRequirements
applicantLocationRequirements.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

application.label: application
application.description: An application that can complete the request.

applicationCategory.label: applicationCategory
applicationCategory.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

applicationContact.label: applicationContact
applicationContact.description: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

applicationDeadline.label: applicationDeadline
applicationDeadline.description: The date at which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

applicationStartDate.label: applicationStartDate
applicationStartDate.description: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

applicationSubCategory.label: applicationSubCategory
applicationSubCategory.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

applicationSuite.label: applicationSuite
applicationSuite.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

appliesToDeliveryMethod.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
appliesToDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

appliesToPaymentMethod.label: appliesToPaymentMethod
appliesToPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

archiveHeld.label: archiveHeld
archiveHeld.description: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

archivedAt.label: archivedAt
archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

area.label: area
area.description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

areaServed.label: areaServed
areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

arrivalAirport.label: arrivalAirport
arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

arrivalBoatTerminal.label: arrivalBoatTerminal
arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

arrivalBusStop.label: arrivalBusStop
arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

arrivalGate.label: arrivalGate
arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

arrivalPlatform.label: arrivalPlatform
arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

arrivalStation.label: arrivalStation
arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

arrivalTerminal.label: arrivalTerminal
arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

artEdition.label: artEdition
artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

artMedium.label: artMedium
artMedium.description: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

arterialBranch.label: arterialBranch
arterialBranch.description: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

artform.label: artform
artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

articleBody.label: articleBody
articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

articleSection.label: articleSection
articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

artist.label: artist
artist.description: The primary artist for a work    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

artworkSurface.label: artworkSurface
artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

asin.label: asin
asin.description: An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

aspect.label: aspect
aspect.description: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

assembly.label: assembly
assembly.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

assesses.label: assesses
assesses.description: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

associatedAnatomy.label: associatedAnatomy
associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

associatedArticle.label: associatedArticle
associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

associatedClaimReview.label: associatedClaimReview
associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

associatedDisease.label: associatedDisease
associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

associatedMedia.label: associatedMedia
associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

associatedMediaReview.label: associatedMediaReview
associatedMediaReview.description: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

associatedPathophysiology.label: associatedPathophysiology
associatedPathophysiology.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

athlete.label: athlete
athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

attendee.label: attendee
attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

audience.label: audience
audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

audienceType.label: audienceType
audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

authenticator.label: authenticator
authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

author.label: author
author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

availability.label: availability
availability.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

availabilityEnds.label: availabilityEnds
availabilityEnds.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

availabilityStarts.label: availabilityStarts
availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

availableAtOrFrom.label: availableAtOrFrom
availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

availableChannel.label: availableChannel
availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

availableDeliveryMethod.label: availableDeliveryMethod
availableDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

availableFrom.label: availableFrom
availableFrom.description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

availableIn.label: availableIn
availableIn.description: The location in which the strength is available.

availableLanguage.label: availableLanguage
availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

availableOnDevice.label: availableOnDevice
availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

availableService.label: availableService
availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

availableStrength.label: availableStrength
availableStrength.description: An available dosage strength for the drug.

availableTest.label: availableTest
availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

availableThrough.label: availableThrough
availableThrough.description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

award.label: award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

awards.label: awards
awards.description: Awards won by or for this item.

awayTeam.label: awayTeam
awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

backstory.label: backstory
backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

bankAccountType.label: bankAccountType
bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

baseSalary.label: baseSalary
baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

bccRecipient.label: bccRecipient
bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

bed.label: bed
bed.description: The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

beforeMedia.label: beforeMedia
beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

beneficiaryBank.label: beneficiaryBank
beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or banks branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiarys bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

benefits.label: benefits
benefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

benefitsSummaryUrl.label: benefitsSummaryUrl
benefitsSummaryUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

bestRating.label: bestRating
bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

billingAddress.label: billingAddress
billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

billingDuration.label: billingDuration
billingDuration.description: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

billingIncrement.label: billingIncrement
billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

billingPeriod.label: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

billingStart.label: billingStart
billingStart.description: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

bioChemInteraction.label: bioChemInteraction
bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

bioChemSimilarity.label: bioChemSimilarity
bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

biologicalRole.label: biologicalRole
biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

biomechnicalClass.label: biomechnicalClass
biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

birthPlace.label: birthPlace
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

bitrate.label: bitrate
bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

blogPost.label: blogPost
blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

blogPosts.label: blogPosts
blogPosts.description: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

bloodSupply.label: bloodSupply
bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

boardingGroup.label: boardingGroup
boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

boardingPolicy.label: boardingPolicy
boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

bodyLocation.label: bodyLocation
bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

bodyType.label: bodyType
bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

bookingAgent.label: bookingAgent
bookingAgent.description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

bookingTime.label: bookingTime
bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

borrower.label: borrower
borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

box.label: box
box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

branch.label: branch
branch.description: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

branchCode.label: branchCode
branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

branchOf.label: branchOf
branchOf.description: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].

brand.label: brand
brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

breadcrumb.label: breadcrumb
breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

breastfeedingWarning.label: breastfeedingWarning
breastfeedingWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

broadcastAffiliateOf.label: broadcastAffiliateOf
broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

broadcastChannelId.label: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

broadcastDisplayName.label: broadcastDisplayName
broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

broadcastFrequency.label: broadcastFrequency
broadcastFrequency.description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequences of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

broadcastFrequencyValue.label: broadcastFrequencyValue
broadcastFrequencyValue.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

broadcastOfEvent.label: broadcastOfEvent
broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

broadcastServiceTier.label: broadcastServiceTier
broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

broadcastSignalModulation.label: broadcastSignalModulation
broadcastSignalModulation.description: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

broadcastSubChannel.label: broadcastSubChannel
broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

broadcastTimezone.label: broadcastTimezone
broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

broadcaster.label: broadcaster
broadcaster.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

broker.label: broker
broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

browserRequirements.label: browserRequirements
browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

busName.label: busName
busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

busNumber.label: busNumber
busNumber.description: The unique identifier for the bus.

businessDays.label: businessDays
businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

businessFunction.label: businessFunction
businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

buyer.label: buyer
buyer.description: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

byArtist.label: byArtist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

byDay.label: byDay
byDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the week on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. May be specified using either [[DayOfWeek]], or alternatively [[Text]] conforming to iCal's syntax for byDay recurrence rules.

byMonth.label: byMonth
byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

byMonthDay.label: byMonthDay
byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

byMonthWeek.label: byMonthWeek
byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

callSign.label: callSign
callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

candidate.label: candidate
candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

caption.label: caption
caption.description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

carbohydrateContent.label: carbohydrateContent
carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

cargoVolume.label: cargoVolume
cargoVolume.description:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

carrier.label: carrier
carrier.description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

carrierRequirements.label: carrierRequirements
carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

cashBack.label: cashBack
cashBack.description: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

catalog.label: catalog
catalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

catalogNumber.label: catalogNumber
catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

category.label: category
category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

causeOf.label: causeOf
causeOf.description: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

ccRecipient.label: ccRecipient
ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

character.label: character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

characterAttribute.label: characterAttribute
characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

characterName.label: characterName
characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

checkinTime.label: checkinTime
checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

checkoutPageURLTemplate.label: checkoutPageURLTemplate
checkoutPageURLTemplate.description: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

checkoutTime.label: checkoutTime
checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

chemicalComposition.label: chemicalComposition
chemicalComposition.description: The chemical composition describes the identity and relative ratio of the chemical elements that make up the substance.

chemicalRole.label: chemicalRole
chemicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

childTaxon.label: childTaxon
childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

cholesterolContent.label: cholesterolContent
cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

circle.label: circle
circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

citation.label: citation
citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

claimInterpreter.label: claimInterpreter
claimInterpreter.description: For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content    sed to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

claimReviewed.label: claimReviewed
claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

clincalPharmacology.label: clincalPharmacology
clincalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

clinicalPharmacology.label: clinicalPharmacology
clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

clipNumber.label: clipNumber
clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

closes.label: closes
closes.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

coach.label: coach
coach.description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

code.label: code
code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

codeRepository.label: codeRepository
codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

codeSampleType.label: codeSampleType
codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

codeValue.label: codeValue
codeValue.description: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

collection.label: collection
collection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

collectionSize.label: collectionSize
collectionSize.description: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

colorist.label: colorist
colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

commentCount.label: commentCount
commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

commentTime.label: commentTime
commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

competencyRequired.label: competencyRequired
competencyRequired.description: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

competitor.label: competitor
competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

composer.label: composer
composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

comprisedOf.label: comprisedOf
comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

conditionsOfAccess.label: conditionsOfAccess
conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

confirmationNumber.label: confirmationNumber
confirmationNumber.description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

connectedTo.label: connectedTo
connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

constraintProperty.label: constraintProperty
constraintProperty.description: Indicates a property used as a constraint. For example, in the definition of a [[StatisticalVariable]]. The value is a property, either from within Schema.org or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

contactOption.label: contactOption
contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

contactPoint.label: contactPoint
contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

contactPoints.label: contactPoints
contactPoints.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

contactType.label: contactType
contactType.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

contactlessPayment.label: contactlessPayment
contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

containedIn.label: containedIn
containedIn.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

containedInPlace.label: containedInPlace
containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

containsPlace.label: containsPlace
containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

containsSeason.label: containsSeason
containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

contentLocation.label: contentLocation
contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

contentRating.label: contentRating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

contentReferenceTime.label: contentReferenceTime
contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

contentType.label: contentType
contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

contentUrl.label: contentUrl
contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

contributor.label: contributor
contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

cookTime.label: cookTime
cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

cookingMethod.label: cookingMethod
cookingMethod.description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

copyrightHolder.label: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

copyrightNotice.label: copyrightNotice
copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

copyrightYear.label: copyrightYear
copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

correction.label: correction
correction.description: Indicates a correction to a [[CreativeWork]], either via a [[CorrectionComment]], textually or in another document.

correctionsPolicy.label: correctionsPolicy
correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsrooms) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

costCategory.label: costCategory
costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

costCurrency.label: costCurrency
costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter) of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

costOrigin.label: costOrigin
costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

costPerUnit.label: costPerUnit
costPerUnit.description: The cost per unit of the drug.

countriesNotSupported.label: countriesNotSupported
countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

countriesSupported.label: countriesSupported
countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

countryOfAssembly.label: countryOfAssembly
countryOfAssembly.description: The place where the product was assembled.

countryOfLastProcessing.label: countryOfLastProcessing
countryOfLastProcessing.description: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

countryOfOrigin.label: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.description: The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

course.label: course
course.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

courseCode.label: courseCode
courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

courseMode.label: courseMode
courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous).

coursePrerequisites.label: coursePrerequisites
coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

courseSchedule.label: courseSchedule
courseSchedule.description: Represents the length and pace of a course, expressed as a [[Schedule]].

courseWorkload.label: courseWorkload
courseWorkload.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

coverageEndTime.label: coverageEndTime
coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

coverageStartTime.label: coverageStartTime
coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

creativeWorkStatus.label: creativeWorkStatus
creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

creator.label: creator
creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

credentialCategory.label: credentialCategory
credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree, certificate, badge, or more specific term.

creditText.label: creditText
creditText.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

creditedTo.label: creditedTo
creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

cssSelector.label: cssSelector
cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

currenciesAccepted.label: currenciesAccepted
currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

currency.label: currency
currency.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

currentExchangeRate.label: currentExchangeRate
currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

customer.label: customer
customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

customerRemorseReturnFees.label: customerRemorseReturnFees
customerRemorseReturnFees.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.label: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.label: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

cutoffTime.label: cutoffTime
cutoffTime.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

cvdCollectionDate.label: cvdCollectionDate
cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

cvdFacilityCounty.label: cvdFacilityCounty
cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

cvdFacilityId.label: cvdFacilityId
cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

cvdNumBeds.label: cvdNumBeds
cvdNumBeds.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

cvdNumBedsOcc.label: cvdNumBedsOcc
cvdNumBedsOcc.description: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

cvdNumC19Died.label: cvdNumC19Died
cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

cvdNumC19HOPats.label: cvdNumC19HOPats
cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

cvdNumC19HospPats.label: cvdNumC19HospPats
cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

cvdNumC19MechVentPats.label: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
cvdNumC19MechVentPats.description: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.label: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

cvdNumC19OverflowPats.label: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
cvdNumC19OverflowPats.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

cvdNumICUBeds.label: cvdNumICUBeds
cvdNumICUBeds.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

cvdNumICUBedsOcc.label: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

cvdNumTotBeds.label: cvdNumTotBeds
cvdNumTotBeds.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

cvdNumVent.label: cvdNumVent
cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

cvdNumVentUse.label: cvdNumVentUse
cvdNumVentUse.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

dataFeedElement.label: dataFeedElement
dataFeedElement.description: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

dataset.label: dataset
dataset.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

datasetTimeInterval.label: datasetTimeInterval
datasetTimeInterval.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

dateCreated.label: dateCreated
dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

dateDeleted.label: dateDeleted
dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

dateIssued.label: dateIssued
dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

dateModified.label: dateModified
dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

datePosted.label: datePosted
datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

dateRead.label: dateRead
dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

dateReceived.label: dateReceived
dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

dateSent.label: dateSent
dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

dateVehicleFirstRegistered.label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
dateVehicleFirstRegistered.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

dateline.label: dateline
dateline.description: A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]].Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

dayOfWeek.label: dayOfWeek
dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

deathPlace.label: deathPlace
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

defaultValue.label: defaultValue
defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

deliveryLeadTime.label: deliveryLeadTime
deliveryLeadTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

deliveryMethod.label: deliveryMethod
deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

deliveryStatus.label: deliveryStatus
deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

deliveryTime.label: deliveryTime
deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

department.label: department
department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

departureAirport.label: departureAirport
departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

departureBoatTerminal.label: departureBoatTerminal
departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

departureBusStop.label: departureBusStop
departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

departureGate.label: departureGate
departureGate.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

departurePlatform.label: departurePlatform
departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

departureStation.label: departureStation
departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

departureTerminal.label: departureTerminal
departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

dependencies.label: dependencies
dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

device.label: device
device.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

diagnosis.label: diagnosis
diagnosis.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

diagram.label: diagram
diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

diet.label: diet
diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

dietFeatures.label: dietFeatures
dietFeatures.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

differentialDiagnosis.label: differentialDiagnosis
differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

directApply.label: directApply
directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

director.label: director
director.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

directors.label: directors
directors.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

disambiguatingDescription.label: disambiguatingDescription
disambiguatingDescription.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

discountCode.label: discountCode
discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

discountCurrency.label: discountCurrency
discountCurrency.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

discusses.label: discusses
discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

discussionUrl.label: discussionUrl
discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

diseaseSpreadStatistics.label: diseaseSpreadStatistics
diseaseSpreadStatistics.description: Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or  described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

dissolutionDate.label: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

distance.label: distance
distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

distinguishingSign.label: distinguishingSign
distinguishingSign.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

distribution.label: distribution
distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

diversityPolicy.label: diversityPolicy
diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsrooms diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

diversityStaffingReport.label: diversityStaffingReport
diversityStaffingReport.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

documentation.label: documentation
documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

doesNotShip.label: doesNotShip
doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

domainIncludes.label: domainIncludes
domainIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

domiciledMortgage.label: domiciledMortgage
domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

dosageForm.label: dosageForm
dosageForm.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

doseSchedule.label: doseSchedule
doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

doseUnit.label: doseUnit
doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

doseValue.label: doseValue
doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

downPayment.label: downPayment
downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

downloadUrl.label: downloadUrl
downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

downvoteCount.label: downvoteCount
downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

drainsTo.label: drainsTo
drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

driveWheelConfiguration.label: driveWheelConfiguration
driveWheelConfiguration.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

dropoffLocation.label: dropoffLocation
dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

dropoffTime.label: dropoffTime
dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

drug.label: drug
drug.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

drugClass.label: drugClass
drugClass.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

drugUnit.label: drugUnit
drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

duns.label: duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

duplicateTherapy.label: duplicateTherapy
duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

duration.label: duration
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

durationOfWarranty.label: durationOfWarranty
durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

duringMedia.label: duringMedia
duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

earlyPrepaymentPenalty.label: earlyPrepaymentPenalty
earlyPrepaymentPenalty.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

editEIDR.label: editEIDR
editEIDR.description: An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

editor.label: editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

eduQuestionType.label: eduQuestionType
eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

educationRequirements.label: educationRequirements
educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

educationalAlignment.label: educationalAlignment
educationalAlignment.description: An alignment to an established educational framework.This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

educationalCredentialAwarded.label: educationalCredentialAwarded
educationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

educationalFramework.label: educationalFramework
educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

educationalLevel.label: educationalLevel
educationalLevel.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

educationalProgramMode.label: educationalProgramMode
educationalProgramMode.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

educationalUse.label: educationalUse
educationalUse.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

elevation.label: elevation
elevation.description: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

eligibilityToWorkRequirement.label: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
eligibilityToWorkRequirement.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

eligibleCustomerType.label: eligibleCustomerType
eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

eligibleDuration.label: eligibleDuration
eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

eligibleQuantity.label: eligibleQuantity
eligibleQuantity.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

eligibleRegion.label: eligibleRegion
eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

eligibleTransactionVolume.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
eligibleTransactionVolume.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

embedUrl.label: embedUrl
embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

embeddedTextCaption.label: embeddedTextCaption
embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

emissionsCO2.label: emissionsCO2
emissionsCO2.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

employerOverview.label: employerOverview
employerOverview.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

employmentType.label: employmentType
employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

employmentUnit.label: employmentUnit
employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

encodesBioChemEntity.label: encodesBioChemEntity
encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

encodesCreativeWork.label: encodesCreativeWork
encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

encoding.label: encoding
encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

encodingFormat.label: encodingFormat
encodingFormat.description: Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

encodingType.label: encodingType
encodingType.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

encodings.label: encodings
encodings.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

endDate.label: endDate
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

endOffset.label: endOffset
endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

endTime.label: endTime
endTime.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

endorsee.label: endorsee
endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

endorsers.label: endorsers
endorsers.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

energyEfficiencyScaleMax.label: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
energyEfficiencyScaleMax.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

energyEfficiencyScaleMin.label: energyEfficiencyScaleMin
energyEfficiencyScaleMin.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

engineDisplacement.label: engineDisplacement
engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

enginePower.label: enginePower
enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 3: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

engineType.label: engineType
engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

entertainmentBusiness.label: entertainmentBusiness
entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

epidemiology.label: epidemiology
epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

episode.label: episode
episode.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

episodeNumber.label: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

episodes.label: episodes
episodes.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

equal.label: equal
equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

error.label: error
error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

estimatedCost.label: estimatedCost
estimatedCost.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

estimatedFlightDuration.label: estimatedFlightDuration
estimatedFlightDuration.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

estimatedSalary.label: estimatedSalary
estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

estimatesRiskOf.label: estimatesRiskOf
estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

ethicsPolicy.label: ethicsPolicy
ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

event.label: event
event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

eventAttendanceMode.label: eventAttendanceMode
