numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

numberOfLoanPayments.label: numberOfLoanPayments
numberOfLoanPayments.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

numberOfPages.label: numberOfPages
numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

numberOfPartialBathrooms.label: numberOfPartialBathrooms
numberOfPartialBathrooms.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and  bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

numberOfPlayers.label: numberOfPlayers
numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

numberOfPreviousOwners.label: numberOfPreviousOwners
numberOfPreviousOwners.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

numberOfRooms.label: numberOfRooms
numberOfRooms.description: The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

numberOfSeasons.label: numberOfSeasons
numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

numberedPosition.label: numberedPosition
numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

nutrition.label: nutrition
nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

object.label: object
object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

observationAbout.label: observationAbout
observationAbout.description: The [[observationAbout]] property identifies an entity, often a [[Place]], associated with an [[Observation]].

observationPeriod.label: observationPeriod
observationPeriod.description: The length of time an Observation took place over. The format follows `P[0-9]*[Y|M|D|h|m|s]`. For example, P1Y is Period 1 Year, P3M is Period 3 Months, P3h is Period 3 hours.

occupancy.label: occupancy
occupancy.description: The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

occupationLocation.label: occupationLocation
occupationLocation.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

occupationalCategory.label: occupationalCategory
occupationalCategory.description: A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\nNote: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

occupationalCredentialAwarded.label: occupationalCredentialAwarded
occupationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

offerCount.label: offerCount
offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

offeredBy.label: offeredBy
offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

offers.label: offers
offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

offersPrescriptionByMail.label: offersPrescriptionByMail
offersPrescriptionByMail.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

openingHours.label: openingHours
openingHours.description: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

openingHoursSpecification.label: openingHoursSpecification
openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

opens.label: opens
opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

operatingSystem.label: operatingSystem
operatingSystem.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

opponent.label: opponent
opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

option.label: option
option.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

orderDelivery.label: orderDelivery
orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

orderItemNumber.label: orderItemNumber
orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

orderItemStatus.label: orderItemStatus
orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

orderQuantity.label: orderQuantity
orderQuantity.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

orderStatus.label: orderStatus
orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

originalMediaContextDescription.label: originalMediaContextDescription
originalMediaContextDescription.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

originalMediaLink.label: originalMediaLink
originalMediaLink.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

originatesFrom.label: originatesFrom
originatesFrom.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

overdosage.label: overdosage
overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

ownedFrom.label: ownedFrom
ownedFrom.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

ownedThrough.label: ownedThrough
ownedThrough.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

ownershipFundingInfo.label: ownershipFundingInfo
ownershipFundingInfo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

owns.label: owns
owns.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

pageEnd.label: pageEnd
pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

pageStart.label: pageStart
pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

pagination.label: pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

parentItem.label: parentItem
parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

parentOrganization.label: parentOrganization
parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

parentService.label: parentService
parentService.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

parentTaxon.label: parentTaxon
parentTaxon.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

partOfEpisode.label: partOfEpisode
partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

partOfInvoice.label: partOfInvoice
partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

partOfOrder.label: partOfOrder
partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

partOfSeason.label: partOfSeason
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

partOfSeries.label: partOfSeries
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

partOfSystem.label: partOfSystem
partOfSystem.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

partOfTVSeries.label: partOfTVSeries
partOfTVSeries.description: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

partOfTrip.label: partOfTrip
partOfTrip.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

participant.label: participant
participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

partySize.label: partySize
partySize.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

passengerPriorityStatus.label: passengerPriorityStatus
passengerPriorityStatus.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

passengerSequenceNumber.label: passengerSequenceNumber
passengerSequenceNumber.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

pathophysiology.label: pathophysiology
pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

pattern.label: pattern
pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

payload.label: payload
payload.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

paymentAccepted.label: paymentAccepted
paymentAccepted.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

paymentDue.label: paymentDue
paymentDue.description: The date that payment is due.

paymentDueDate.label: paymentDueDate
paymentDueDate.description: The date that payment is due.

paymentMethod.label: paymentMethod
paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

paymentMethodId.label: paymentMethodId
paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

paymentStatus.label: paymentStatus
paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

paymentUrl.label: paymentUrl
paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

penciler.label: penciler
penciler.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

performTime.label: performTime
performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

performer.label: performer
performer.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

performerIn.label: performerIn
performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

performers.label: performers
performers.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

permissionType.label: permissionType
permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

permissions.label: permissions
permissions.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

permitAudience.label: permitAudience
permitAudience.description: The target audience for this permit.

permittedUsage.label: permittedUsage
permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

petsAllowed.label: petsAllowed
petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

phoneticText.label: phoneticText
phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /hjustn/.

physicalRequirement.label: physicalRequirement
physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

physiologicalBenefits.label: physiologicalBenefits
physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

pickupLocation.label: pickupLocation
pickupLocation.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

pickupTime.label: pickupTime
pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

playMode.label: playMode
playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

playerType.label: playerType
playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

playersOnline.label: playersOnline
playersOnline.description: Number of players on the server.

polygon.label: polygon
polygon.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

populationType.label: populationType
populationType.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

position.label: position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

positiveNotes.label: positiveNotes
positiveNotes.description: Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).

possibleComplication.label: possibleComplication
possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

possibleTreatment.label: possibleTreatment
possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

postOfficeBoxNumber.label: postOfficeBoxNumber
postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

postOp.label: postOp
postOp.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

postalCodeBegin.label: postalCodeBegin
postalCodeBegin.description: First postal code in a range (included).

postalCodeEnd.label: postalCodeEnd
postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

postalCodePrefix.label: postalCodePrefix
postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

postalCodeRange.label: postalCodeRange
postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

potentialAction.label: potentialAction
potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

potentialUse.label: potentialUse
potentialUse.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

preOp.label: preOp
preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

predecessorOf.label: predecessorOf
predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

pregnancyWarning.label: pregnancyWarning
pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

prepTime.label: prepTime
prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

preparation.label: preparation
preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

prescribingInfo.label: prescribingInfo
prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

prescriptionStatus.label: prescriptionStatus
prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

previousItem.label: previousItem
previousItem.description: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

previousStartDate.label: previousStartDate
previousStartDate.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

price.label: price
price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

priceComponent.label: priceComponent
priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

priceComponentType.label: priceComponentType
priceComponentType.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

priceCurrency.label: priceCurrency
priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

priceRange.label: priceRange
priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

priceSpecification.label: priceSpecification
priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

priceType.label: priceType
priceType.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEnumeration.

priceValidUntil.label: priceValidUntil
priceValidUntil.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

primaryImageOfPage.label: primaryImageOfPage
primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

primaryPrevention.label: primaryPrevention
primaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

printColumn.label: printColumn
printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

printEdition.label: printEdition
printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

printPage.label: printPage
printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

printSection.label: printSection
printSection.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

procedure.label: procedure
procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

procedureType.label: procedureType
procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

processingTime.label: processingTime
processingTime.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

processorRequirements.label: processorRequirements
processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

producer.label: producer
producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

produces.label: produces
produces.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

productGroupID.label: productGroupID
productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

productID.label: productID
productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

productReturnDays.label: productReturnDays
productReturnDays.description: The productReturnDays property indicates the number of days (from purchase) within which relevant product return policy is applicable.

productReturnLink.label: productReturnLink
productReturnLink.description: Indicates a Web page or service by URL, for product return.

productSupported.label: productSupported
productSupported.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

productionCompany.label: productionCompany
productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

productionDate.label: productionDate
productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

proficiencyLevel.label: proficiencyLevel
proficiencyLevel.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

programMembershipUsed.label: programMembershipUsed
programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

programPrerequisites.label: programPrerequisites
programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

programType.label: programType
programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

programmingModel.label: programmingModel
programmingModel.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

propertyID.label: propertyID
propertyID.description: A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3)a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

proprietaryName.label: proprietaryName
proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

proteinContent.label: proteinContent
proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

provider.label: provider
provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

providerMobility.label: providerMobility
providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

providesBroadcastService.label: providesBroadcastService
providesBroadcastService.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

providesService.label: providesService
providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

publicAccess.label: publicAccess
publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value

publication.label: publication
publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

publicationType.label: publicationType
publicationType.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

publishedBy.label: publishedBy
publishedBy.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

publishedOn.label: publishedOn
publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

publisher.label: publisher
publisher.description: The publisher of the creative work.

publisherImprint.label: publisherImprint
publisherImprint.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

publishingPrinciples.label: publishingPrinciples
publishingPrinciples.description: The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

purchaseDate.label: purchaseDate
purchaseDate.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

qualifications.label: qualifications
qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

quarantineGuidelines.label: quarantineGuidelines
quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

query.label: query
query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

quest.label: quest
quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

question.label: question
question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

rangeIncludes.label: rangeIncludes
rangeIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

ratingCount.label: ratingCount
ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

ratingExplanation.label: ratingExplanation
ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

ratingValue.label: ratingValue
ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

readBy.label: readBy
readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

readonlyValue.label: readonlyValue
readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

realEstateAgent.label: realEstateAgent
realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

recipe.label: recipe
recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

recipeCategory.label: recipeCategory
recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipefor example, appetizer, entree, etc.

recipeCuisine.label: recipeCuisine
recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

recipeIngredient.label: recipeIngredient
recipeIngredient.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

recipeInstructions.label: recipeInstructions
recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

recipeYield.label: recipeYield
recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

recipient.label: recipient
recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

recognizedBy.label: recognizedBy
recognizedBy.description: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

recognizingAuthority.label: recognizingAuthority
recognizingAuthority.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

recommendationStrength.label: recommendationStrength
recommendationStrength.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

recommendedIntake.label: recommendedIntake
recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

recordLabel.label: recordLabel
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

recordedAs.label: recordedAs
recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

recordedAt.label: recordedAt
recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

recordedIn.label: recordedIn
recordedIn.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

recordingOf.label: recordingOf
recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

recourseLoan.label: recourseLoan
recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

referenceQuantity.label: referenceQuantity
referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

referencesOrder.label: referencesOrder
referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

refundType.label: refundType
refundType.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

regionDrained.label: regionDrained
regionDrained.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

regionsAllowed.label: regionsAllowed
regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

relatedAnatomy.label: relatedAnatomy
relatedAnatomy.description: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

relatedCondition.label: relatedCondition
relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

relatedDrug.label: relatedDrug
relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

relatedLink.label: relatedLink
relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

relatedStructure.label: relatedStructure
relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

relatedTherapy.label: relatedTherapy
relatedTherapy.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

releaseDate.label: releaseDate
releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

releaseNotes.label: releaseNotes
releaseNotes.description: Description of what changed in this version.

releaseOf.label: releaseOf
releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

releasedEvent.label: releasedEvent
releasedEvent.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

relevantSpecialty.label: relevantSpecialty
relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

remainingAttendeeCapacity.label: remainingAttendeeCapacity
remainingAttendeeCapacity.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

renegotiableLoan.label: renegotiableLoan
renegotiableLoan.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

repeatCount.label: repeatCount
repeatCount.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

repeatFrequency.label: repeatFrequency
repeatFrequency.description: Defines the frequency at which [[Event]]s will occur according to a schedule [[Schedule]]. The intervals between      events should be defined as a [[Duration]] of time.

repetitions.label: repetitions
repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

replacee.label: replacee
replacee.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

replacer.label: replacer
replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

replyToUrl.label: replyToUrl
replyToUrl.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

reportNumber.label: reportNumber
reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

representativeOfPage.label: representativeOfPage
representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

requiredCollateral.label: requiredCollateral
requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

requiredGender.label: requiredGender
requiredGender.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

requiredMaxAge.label: requiredMaxAge
requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

requiredMinAge.label: requiredMinAge
requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

requiredQuantity.label: requiredQuantity
requiredQuantity.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

requirements.label: requirements
requirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

requiresSubscription.label: requiresSubscription
requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

reservationFor.label: reservationFor
reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

reservationId.label: reservationId
reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

reservationStatus.label: reservationStatus
reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

reservedTicket.label: reservedTicket
reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

responsibilities.label: responsibilities
responsibilities.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

restPeriods.label: restPeriods
restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

restockingFee.label: restockingFee
restockingFee.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

result.label: result
result.description: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

resultComment.label: resultComment
resultComment.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

resultReview.label: resultReview
resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

returnFees.label: returnFees
returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

returnLabelSource.label: returnLabelSource
returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

returnMethod.label: returnMethod
returnMethod.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

returnPolicyCategory.label: returnPolicyCategory
returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

returnPolicyCountry.label: returnPolicyCountry
returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

returnPolicySeasonalOverride.label: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
returnPolicySeasonalOverride.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

returnShippingFeesAmount.label: returnShippingFeesAmount
returnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

reviewAspect.label: reviewAspect
reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

reviewBody.label: reviewBody
reviewBody.description: The actual body of the review.

reviewCount.label: reviewCount
reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

reviewRating.label: reviewRating
reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

reviewedBy.label: reviewedBy
reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

riskFactor.label: riskFactor
riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

risks.label: risks
risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

roleName.label: roleName
roleName.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

roofLoad.label: roofLoad
roofLoad.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

rsvpResponse.label: rsvpResponse
rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

runsTo.label: runsTo
runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

runtime.label: runtime
runtime.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

runtimePlatform.label: runtimePlatform
runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

rxcui.label: rxcui
rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

safetyConsideration.label: safetyConsideration
safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

salaryCurrency.label: salaryCurrency
salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

salaryUponCompletion.label: salaryUponCompletion
salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

sameAs.label: sameAs
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

sampleType.label: sampleType
sampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

saturatedFatContent.label: saturatedFatContent
saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

scheduleTimezone.label: scheduleTimezone
scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

scheduledPaymentDate.label: scheduledPaymentDate
scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

scheduledTime.label: scheduledTime
scheduledTime.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

schemaVersion.label: schemaVersion
schemaVersion.description: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

screenCount.label: screenCount
screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

screenshot.label: screenshot
screenshot.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

sdDatePublished.label: sdDatePublished
sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]]

sdLicense.label: sdLicense
sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

sdPublisher.label: sdPublisher
sdPublisher.description: Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

season.label: season
season.description: A season in a media series.

seasonNumber.label: seasonNumber
seasonNumber.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

seasons.label: seasons
seasons.description: A season in a media series.

seatNumber.label: seatNumber
seatNumber.description: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

seatRow.label: seatRow
seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

seatSection.label: seatSection
seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

seatingCapacity.label: seatingCapacity
seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons

secondaryPrevention.label: secondaryPrevention
secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

securityClearanceRequirement.label: securityClearanceRequirement
securityClearanceRequirement.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

securityScreening.label: securityScreening
securityScreening.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

seeks.label: seeks
seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

seller.label: seller
seller.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

sender.label: sender
sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

sensoryRequirement.label: sensoryRequirement
sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

sensoryUnit.label: sensoryUnit
sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

serialNumber.label: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

seriousAdverseOutcome.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
seriousAdverseOutcome.description: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

serviceArea.label: serviceArea
serviceArea.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

serviceAudience.label: serviceAudience
serviceAudience.description: The audience eligible for this service.

serviceLocation.label: serviceLocation
serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

serviceOperator.label: serviceOperator
serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

serviceOutput.label: serviceOutput
serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

servicePhone.label: servicePhone
servicePhone.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

servicePostalAddress.label: servicePostalAddress
servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

serviceSmsNumber.label: serviceSmsNumber
serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

serviceType.label: serviceType
serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

serviceUrl.label: serviceUrl
serviceUrl.description: The website to access the service.

servingSize.label: servingSize
servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

sha256.label: sha256
sha256.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'

sharedContent.label: sharedContent
sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

shippingDestination.label: shippingDestination
shippingDestination.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

shippingDetails.label: shippingDetails
shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

shippingLabel.label: shippingLabel
shippingLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[ShippingRateSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

shippingOrigin.label: shippingOrigin
shippingOrigin.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

shippingRate.label: shippingRate
shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

shippingSettingsLink.label: shippingSettingsLink
shippingSettingsLink.description: Link to a page containing [[ShippingRateSettings]] and [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] details.

signDetected.label: signDetected
signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

signOrSymptom.label: signOrSymptom
signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

significance.label: significance
significance.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

significantLink.label: significantLink
significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

significantLinks.label: significantLinks
significantLinks.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

size.label: size
size.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

sizeGroup.label: sizeGroup
sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular"

sizeSystem.label: sizeSystem
sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

skills.label: skills
skills.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

sku.label: sku
sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

slogan.label: slogan
slogan.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

smiles.label: smiles
smiles.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

smokingAllowed.label: smokingAllowed
smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

sodiumContent.label: sodiumContent
sodiumContent.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

softwareAddOn.label: softwareAddOn
softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

softwareRequirements.label: softwareRequirements
softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

sourceOrganization.label: sourceOrganization
sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

sourcedFrom.label: sourcedFrom
sourcedFrom.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

spatial.label: spatial
spatial.description: The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties(e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

spatialCoverage.label: spatialCoverage
spatialCoverage.description: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

speakable.label: speakable
speakable.description: Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For thiswe define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

specialCommitments.label: specialCommitments
specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

specialOpeningHoursSpecification.label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
specialOpeningHoursSpecification.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

specialty.label: specialty
specialty.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

speechToTextMarkup.label: speechToTextMarkup
speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

speed.label: speed
speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

spokenByCharacter.label: spokenByCharacter
spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

sponsor.label: sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

sportsActivityLocation.label: sportsActivityLocation
sportsActivityLocation.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

sportsEvent.label: sportsEvent
sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

sportsTeam.label: sportsTeam
sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

stage.label: stage
stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

stageAsNumber.label: stageAsNumber
stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

starRating.label: starRating
starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

startDate.label: startDate
startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

startOffset.label: startOffset
startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

startTime.label: startTime
startTime.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

statType.label: statType
statType.description: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[count]], [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

steeringPosition.label: steeringPosition
steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

step.label: step
step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

stepValue.label: stepValue
stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

steps.label: steps
steps.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

streetAddress.label: streetAddress
streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

strengthUnit.label: strengthUnit
strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

strengthValue.label: strengthValue
strengthValue.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

structuralClass.label: structuralClass
structuralClass.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

study.label: study
study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

studyDesign.label: studyDesign
studyDesign.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

studyLocation.label: studyLocation
studyLocation.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

studySubject.label: studySubject
studySubject.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

stupidProperty.label: stupidProperty
stupidProperty.description: This is a StupidProperty! - for testing only

subEvent.label: subEvent
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

subEvents.label: subEvents
subEvents.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

subOrganization.label: subOrganization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

subReservation.label: subReservation
subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

subStageSuffix.label: subStageSuffix
subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

subStructure.label: subStructure
subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

subTest.label: subTest
subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

subTrip.label: subTrip
subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

subjectOf.label: subjectOf
subjectOf.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

subtitleLanguage.label: subtitleLanguage
subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

successorOf.label: successorOf
successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

sugarContent.label: sugarContent
sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

suggestedAge.label: suggestedAge
suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

suggestedAnswer.label: suggestedAnswer
suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

suggestedGender.label: suggestedGender
suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

suggestedMaxAge.label: suggestedMaxAge
suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

suggestedMeasurement.label: suggestedMeasurement
suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

suggestedMinAge.label: suggestedMinAge
suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

suitableForDiet.label: suitableForDiet
suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

superEvent.label: superEvent
superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

supersededBy.label: supersededBy
supersededBy.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

supply.label: supply
supply.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

supplyTo.label: supplyTo
supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

surface.label: surface
surface.description: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

syllabusSections.label: syllabusSections
syllabusSections.description: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

target.label: target
target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

targetCollection.label: targetCollection
targetCollection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

targetDescription.label: targetDescription
targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

targetName.label: targetName
targetName.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

targetPlatform.label: targetPlatform
targetPlatform.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

targetPopulation.label: targetPopulation
targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

targetProduct.label: targetProduct
targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

targetUrl.label: targetUrl
targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

taxID.label: taxID
taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

taxonRank.label: taxonRank
taxonRank.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary  typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs.

taxonomicRange.label: taxonomicRange
taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

teaches.label: teaches
teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

temporal.label: temporal
temporal.description: The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

temporalCoverage.label: temporalCoverage
temporalCoverage.description: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

termCode.label: termCode
termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]]

termDuration.label: termDuration
termDuration.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

termsPerYear.label: termsPerYear
termsPerYear.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

text.label: text
text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

thumbnail.label: thumbnail
thumbnail.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

thumbnailUrl.label: thumbnailUrl
thumbnailUrl.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

tickerSymbol.label: tickerSymbol
tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

ticketNumber.label: ticketNumber
ticketNumber.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

ticketToken.label: ticketToken
ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

ticketedSeat.label: ticketedSeat
ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

timeOfDay.label: timeOfDay
timeOfDay.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

timeRequired.label: timeRequired
timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.

timeToComplete.label: timeToComplete
timeToComplete.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

tissueSample.label: tissueSample
tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

titleEIDR.label: titleEIDR
titleEIDR.description: An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

toLocation.label: toLocation
toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

toRecipient.label: toRecipient
toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

tocContinuation.label: tocContinuation
tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

tongueWeight.label: tongueWeight
tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

tool.label: tool
tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

torque.label: torque
torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

totalHistoricalEnrollment.label: totalHistoricalEnrollment
totalHistoricalEnrollment.description: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

totalJobOpenings.label: totalJobOpenings
totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

totalPrice.label: totalPrice
totalPrice.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

totalTime.label: totalTime
totalTime.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

tourBookingPage.label: tourBookingPage
tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

touristType.label: touristType
touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

track.label: track
track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

trackingUrl.label: trackingUrl
trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

tracks.label: tracks
tracks.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

trailer.label: trailer
trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

trailerWeight.label: trailerWeight
trailerWeight.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

trainName.label: trainName
