trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

trainNumber.label: trainNumber
trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

trainingSalary.label: trainingSalary
trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

transFatContent.label: transFatContent
transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

transcript.label: transcript
transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

transitTime.label: transitTime
transitTime.description: The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

transitTimeLabel.label: transitTimeLabel
transitTimeLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

translationOfWork.label: translationOfWork
translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g.  is a translationOf On the Origin of Species.

translator.label: translator
translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

transmissionMethod.label: transmissionMethod
transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

travelBans.label: travelBans
travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

tributary.label: tributary
tributary.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

tripOrigin.label: tripOrigin
tripOrigin.description: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

typeOfBed.label: typeOfBed
typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

typeOfGood.label: typeOfGood
typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

typicalAgeRange.label: typicalAgeRange
typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

typicalCreditsPerTerm.label: typicalCreditsPerTerm
typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

typicalTest.label: typicalTest
typicalTest.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

underName.label: underName
underName.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

unitCode.label: unitCode
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

unitText.label: unitText
unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code forunitCode.

unnamedSourcesPolicy.label: unnamedSourcesPolicy
unnamedSourcesPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

unsaturatedFatContent.label: unsaturatedFatContent
unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

uploadDate.label: uploadDate
uploadDate.description: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

upvoteCount.label: upvoteCount
upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

urlTemplate.label: urlTemplate
urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

usageInfo.label: usageInfo
usageInfo.description: The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

usedToDiagnose.label: usedToDiagnose
usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

userInteractionCount.label: userInteractionCount
userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

usesDevice.label: usesDevice
usesDevice.description: Device used to perform the test.

usesHealthPlanIdStandard.label: usesHealthPlanIdStandard
usesHealthPlanIdStandard.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

utterances.label: utterances
utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

validFor.label: validFor
validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

validFrom.label: validFrom
validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

validIn.label: validIn
validIn.description: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

validThrough.label: validThrough
validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

validUntil.label: validUntil
validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

value.label: value
value.description:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

valueAddedTaxIncluded.label: valueAddedTaxIncluded
valueAddedTaxIncluded.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

valueMaxLength.label: valueMaxLength
valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

valueMinLength.label: valueMinLength
valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

valueName.label: valueName
valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

valuePattern.label: valuePattern
valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

valueReference.label: valueReference
valueReference.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

valueRequired.label: valueRequired
valueRequired.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

variableMeasured.label: variableMeasured
variableMeasured.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue, or more explicitly as a [[StatisticalVariable]].

variablesMeasured.label: variablesMeasured
variablesMeasured.description: Originally named [[variablesMeasured]], the [[variableMeasured]] property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue.

variantCover.label: variantCover
variantCover.description: A description of the variant cover    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

variesBy.label: variesBy
variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

vatID.label: vatID
vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

vehicleConfiguration.label: vehicleConfiguration
vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

vehicleEngine.label: vehicleEngine
vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

vehicleIdentificationNumber.label: vehicleIdentificationNumber
vehicleIdentificationNumber.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

vehicleInteriorColor.label: vehicleInteriorColor
vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

vehicleInteriorType.label: vehicleInteriorType
vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

vehicleModelDate.label: vehicleModelDate
vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

vehicleSeatingCapacity.label: vehicleSeatingCapacity
vehicleSeatingCapacity.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

vehicleSpecialUsage.label: vehicleSpecialUsage
vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

vehicleTransmission.label: vehicleTransmission
vehicleTransmission.description: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

verificationFactCheckingPolicy.label: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
verificationFactCheckingPolicy.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

version.label: version
version.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

videoFormat.label: videoFormat
videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

videoFrameSize.label: videoFrameSize
videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

volumeNumber.label: volumeNumber
volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

warning.label: warning
warning.description: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

warranty.label: warranty
warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

warrantyPromise.label: warrantyPromise
warrantyPromise.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

warrantyScope.label: warrantyScope
warrantyScope.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

webCheckinTime.label: webCheckinTime
webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

webFeed.label: webFeed
webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

weight.label: weight
weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

weightTotal.label: weightTotal
weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

wheelbase.label: wheelbase
wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet

winner.label: winner
winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

wordCount.label: wordCount
wordCount.description: The number of words in the text of the Article.

workExample.label: workExample
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

workFeatured.label: workFeatured
workFeatured.description: A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

workHours.label: workHours
workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

workLocation.label: workLocation
workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

workPerformed.label: workPerformed
workPerformed.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

workPresented.label: workPresented
workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

workTranslation.label: workTranslation
workTranslation.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. E.g.  has an English workTranslation Journey to the West, a German workTranslation Monkeys Pilgerfahrt and a Vietnamese  translation Ty du k bnh kho.

workload.label: workload
workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

worksFor.label: worksFor
worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.

worstRating.label: worstRating
worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

xpath.label: xpath
xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

yearBuilt.label: yearBuilt
yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

yearlyRevenue.label: yearlyRevenue
yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

yield.label: yield
yield.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.
